--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PREAMBLE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Work is a deterministic-first framework for issuing investment-related
responses through systems that combine large language models with auditable
provenance gates. It is published under this License to advance professional
practice, transparency, and the fiduciary standard articulated by the CFA
Institute Code of Ethics and Standards of Professional Conduct.

Conversational language-model systems, used in isolation, are not suitable
for the discharge of fiduciary duties. This License grants permissive rights
to use the Work, conditioned on preservation of the deterministic gates and
disclosures that make the Work auditable. This License is "Source-Available
· Ethics-Restricted" and is NOT an Open Source license under the Open Source
Initiative's definition.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
§1. DEFINITIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"License"            means the terms and conditions of this Aura Ethics
                     License v1.0.

"Work"               means the source code, configuration, documentation,
                     system instructions, evaluation harnesses, and synthetic
                     seed data made available under this License.

"Derivative Work"    means any modification, translation, port, or work based
                     on the Work, excluding works that merely link to,
                     interoperate with, or invoke the Work via stable APIs.

"You" or "Licensee"  means any individual or legal entity exercising rights
                     under this License, including their employees and agents
                     acting on their behalf.

"Creator"            means Ian Gilbert, the original author of the Work, and
                     for the purposes of §6 includes Ian Gilbert in any
                     personal, employed, contracted, or successor capacity.

"Confidential Data"  means: (i) client identifiers, account data, or
                     portfolio holdings of any natural or legal person;
                     (ii) proprietary Capital Market Assumption inputs
                     licensed from third-party vendors; (iii) personally
                     identifiable information of any natural person;
                     (iv) any data classified as Confidential under the
                     then-current information security policy of any
                     organization that has lawfully acquired such data.

"Fiduciary System"   means any system that issues output to a third party
                     in connection with the offer, sale, recommendation,
                     analysis, or management of securities, investment
                     strategies, or asset allocation.

"Provenance Gates"   means the deterministic gates shipped with the Work,
                     comprising at minimum: (a) Human-in-the-Loop ("HITL")
                     classification of partition labels at intake; (b)
                     Row-Level Security ("RLS") partition enforcement at
                     the data layer; (c) source pointer hash binding for
                     every numeric claim; (d) truth-table validation
                     before output; and (e) fail-closed routing of
                     unsourced claims to qualified human review.

"CFA Standards"      means the CFA Institute Code of Ethics and Standards
                     of Professional Conduct (I through VII), as amended
                     from time to time, available at cfainstitute.org.


