--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
§4. CONDITIONS OF USE — ETHICS ADDENDUM
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The rights granted in §2 and §3 are conditioned on Your compliance with
each of the following obligations. These obligations are binding on
developers and users of the Work alike.

§4.1  Supervision.  If You use, modify, or distribute the Work as a
      component of any Fiduciary System, that Fiduciary System shall
      operate under the supervision of a CFA charterholder or an
      equivalent fiduciary professional licensed in the jurisdiction in
      which the Fiduciary System is deployed.

§4.2  Disclosure.  If output of a Fiduciary System incorporating the Work
      is delivered to a client, prospective client, or other third party,
      You shall ensure that the involvement of language-model components
      in producing or shaping such output is disclosed in a manner
      reasonably calculated to reach the recipient. The form, granularity,
      and audience of such disclosure may vary (see §4.2.1).

§4.2.1 Audience-Tiered Disclosure.  Nothing in this License requires
      disclosure of internal model identifiers, prompt text, or proprietary
      implementation details to external recipients. Disclosure under §4.2
      is satisfied by a statement that the output is the product of a
      reviewed, AI-assisted process operating under CFA-aligned controls.
      Internal disclosure to qualified reviewers, auditors, and regulators
      shall be more granular and shall include the Provenance Gates'
      decision records sufficient to reconstruct the output.

§4.3  Provenance Preservation.  You shall preserve the Provenance Gates
      shipped with the Work in any Fiduciary System You deploy, or
      replace them with functionally equivalent gates that meet or exceed
      the same audit standard. You shall not strip, disable, or
      circumvent any Provenance Gate as a means of producing output that
      would otherwise fail validation.

§4.4  No Deception.  You shall not use the Work to generate, distribute,
      or shape any communication that misrepresents the role of
      automated systems in producing such communication, or that is
      designed to evade applicable disclosure obligations under CFA
      Standards V(B), V(C), or analogous regimes.

§4.5  CFA Standard VII Compliance.  If You hold the CFA charter, are a
      CFA candidate, or otherwise hold Yourself out as a CFA Institute
      member or member-in-training, Your use of the Work shall comply
      with CFA Standard VII (Responsibilities as a CFA Institute Member
      or CFA Candidate) regardless of any contrary direction from Your
      employer.

§4.6  Faith-Stance Neutrality.  The Work supports configurable faith-based
      and secular partitioning of its knowledge corpus. This License is
      neutral as to faith stance. You shall not use the Work to ridicule,
      attack, or systematically disadvantage any faith community whose
      screening criteria are supported by the Work's partitioning system.

§4.7  Open-Weights Compatibility.  The conditions of this §4 apply
      regardless of whether the language-model component invoked by the
      Work is proprietary, hosted, or open-weights, provided that the
      Provenance Gates remain in force.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
§5. TAMPER-EVIDENT RECEIPTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Any output of a Fiduciary System incorporating the Work that is delivered
to a third party shall carry, or shall be accompanied on request by, a
machine-readable receipt comprising at minimum: (i) the source pointer
hashes for all numeric claims in the output; (ii) the RLS partition
identifier in effect during retrieval; (iii) the decision records of all
Provenance Gates that fired during composition; and (iv) the version
identifier of the Work used to produce the output.

You may equivalently use a receipt of Your own design that records the
same audit substance.


