--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
§7. DATA SEGREGATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This License grants rights to the source code, configuration schemas,
system instructions, evaluation harnesses, design tokens, and synthetic
seed data comprising the Work. No rights are granted to Confidential
Data, which is excluded from the Work by definition.

Any corpus, dataset, or benchmark distributed in or with the Work shall
consist solely of (i) synthetic examples generated for testing purposes;
(ii) public examples whose redistribution is authorized by their original
license; or (iii) examples explicitly approved for public release by all
parties with rights in the underlying data.

Where the Work originally operated against Confidential Data within an
organization's infrastructure, redistribution of equivalent functionality
under this License requires substitution of synthetic, public, or approved
data of equivalent shape. Hashing, tokenization, or other masking of
Confidential Data does not, by itself, convert such data into data
licensable under this License; masking is a privacy control, not a license
grant.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
§8. TERMINATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The rights granted under this License shall terminate automatically upon
any material breach of §4 or §5 that is not cured within thirty (30) days
of Your receipt of written notice of such breach from any party with
standing to assert the breach (including the Creator, an affected client,
or a regulator with jurisdiction).

Upon termination, You shall cease all use, distribution, and Derivative
Work preparation of the Work, and shall not initiate any new Fiduciary
System incorporating the Work. Termination does not affect the validity
of receipts already delivered under §5 nor obligations of disclosure
already triggered under §4.2.

The Creator's rights under §6 are not affected by termination of any
other party's rights under this License.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
§9. PUBLIC AUDIT RIGHT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Any natural or legal person may request, in writing, that the operator of
a deployed Fiduciary System incorporating the Work provide:

  (a) the version identifier of the Work in use;
  (b) the system instructions configured for each persona;
  (c) the Provenance Gate rule packs in force; and
  (d) summary benchmark scores from the most recent eval cycle.

The operator shall respond within thirty (30) days. The operator may
withhold (i) Confidential Data, (ii) information whose disclosure would
violate applicable law, and (iii) information whose disclosure would
compromise the security of the system itself, but shall identify the
categories withheld. This obligation echoes CFA Standard III(D) on
Performance Presentation.


